The paper deals with the computational geometry problem of finding the expected complexity of the union of random Minkowski sums of convex sets, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of probability density functions and the analysis of the expected complexity suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The application of the results to network vulnerability analysis further supports the inclusion in the cs.SI sub-category.
